Brazilian Stock Movers: Grupo Pao de Acucar, OGX, PDG Realty

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-07-12T14:08:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/brazilian-stock-movers-grupo-pao-de-acucar-ogx-pdg-realty.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:50 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.2 percent to 60,350.75.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar (PCAR4
BS) dropped 1 percent to 65.66 reais.  Casino Guichard Perrachon
SA (CO) ’s board said a proposal by Banco BTG Pactual SA’s investment
fund Gama to merge Pao de Acucar with Carrefour SA’s  Brazil  unit
is contrary to its own and investors’ interests. The proposal
overestimated potential cost savings, Casino said in an e-mailed
statement, following a board meeting.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS) declined 0.5
percent to 14.30 reais.  Oil prices  fell after a report showed
 China ’s net imports of crude dropped to an eight-month low in
June.  PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes (PDGR3 BS)
gained 1.7 percent to 8.24 reais. Brazil’s biggest homebuilder
by revenue reported second-quarter net sales of 1.82 billion
reais ($1.16 billion), a 17 percent increase from a year
earlier, according to a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
